    "body": "Hey Sebastian,\n\n  In order to mine, your node needs to generate the full DAG, which is over 1 GB in size, so unless you have significantly more than that (I think during DAG generation it can use up to 4GB RAM), you won't be able to mine. Similarly though, an RPI won't be able to do much, as the network's hashrate is equivalent to literally millions (if not billions) of RPIs :)\n",
